node.text:
I am thrilled to introduce the first class of Sparkle On Scholars! ✨ With almost 150 applications from exceptional @nationalmtb student athletes across the country, this selection process was challenging to say the least. But these four student athletes really shined. They are joyful and hardworking in their pursuit of their personal goals on and off the bike, but show an equally powerful commitment to becoming advocates and leaders in the cycling community. I can’t wait to work with them and help support their efforts as  they transition to becoming collegiate student athletes! 

Meet the scholars: @darciebushee @toby_hassett @justinpeck03 @gwen_sepp

Thank you so much to my sponsors, NICA and the many hands and hearts that went into making this opportunity possible. A special shout out to Casey at NICA, my super star mom and co-chair Maggie and the entire selection committee for the countless hours you dedicated to this project. Bikes can open a lot of doors. This is just the beginning! #sparkleon #nationalmtb #morekidsonbikes 

@bikeonscott @srammtb @rockshox @syncrosbike

This vehicle was designed by @frischi_nextlevel to be my race day set up — but has also enabled a lot of weekend adventures and even this emergency clean air training camp. Grateful to have such a fun adventure mobile and can’t wait to take it back to the races next season! 💃🏻✨ #vanlife #sparklewatts #sendtobend  A huge thank you to @eric_lagerstrom for putting this video together!

node.text: I could not be more excited to announce the release of the @teachaids Crash Course Brain Fly-Through. As an athlete, I have suffered multiple concussions and know how scary, confusing and frustrating they can be. I have also seen how reporting your injury, getting accurate information, and taking recovery seriously can make all the difference. I first got involved in this project as an undergrad at Stanford when I had Piya Sorcar as a professor and it is so meaningful to be able to continue my involvement as an athlete. Please watch this video and share it with your kids - research and education are the most important tools we have to understand and combat the long lasting impacts of head injuries ❤️ #protectyourbrain #crashcourse #science 🤓

node.text: Train hard, recover harder 👊🏽🔥 Using @whoop to track my recovery and sleep has given me real data to understand the role of rest in achieving my best performances. It sounds simple but it’s sometimes the hardest thing! This year my #RESTolution is to become even more of a nap queen and prioritize my mental and physical recovery between big blocks 😴🧘🏻‍♀️ What’s yours? #napqueen #restolution #inthegreen

node.text: Let the games begin 🇺🇸✨🇯🇵 It was a wild adventure getting here with all the paperwork and tests - not to mention the last year of waiting for this moment to hopefully come. Just being here feels like a huge victory and privilege. Soaking it all in! 😍 #trailtotokyo #wemadeit #sparklewatts

node.text: Ciao mi amore ❤️ Training camp in Tuscany was such a special time, particularly because I got to have @willrpatterson by my side every day. There is something magical about going all in on a goal with the people you love and our team created such a unique and positive atmosphere for our final prep. If there is anything I have learned from Nino and Frischi, it’s that your mindset at big events is just as important as your training. Heading to Tokyo feeling loved, grateful and prepared as hell 🛵✨ P.s. stay tuned for the story on this Vespa… it’s a good one #italianliving #allin #keepitfun #gritgracegratitude #LFG
